Dialogue: 0,0:00:15.89,0:00:19.33,Default - italics,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Every once in a while, \NI remember that sword fight.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:21.42,0:00:22.41,Default - italics,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,That day,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:22.81,0:00:26.02,Default - italics,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I lost my answer and simultaneously found it.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:26.73,0:00:29.69,Default - italics,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,But not a single thing has changed.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:31.15,0:00:36.43,Default - italics,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,In my fading memories, I see us. \NHe's still him, and I'm still me.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:37.41,0:00:39.16,Default - italics,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,It's not like I believed that
Dialogue: 0,0:00:39.16,0:00:42.41,Default - italics,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,as a result of that fight, \Nanything would change with us.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:45.50,0:00:46.94,Default - italics,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,It's been two years since then.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:47.92,0:00:50.69,Default - italics,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I came face to face with my ideal.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:51.46,0:00:52.69,Default - italics,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I won't get my answer
Dialogue: 0,0:00:53.68,0:00:55.84,Default - italics,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,for a long, long time yet.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:10.13,0:01:14.51,Title,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(275,562)}#25     Epilogue
Dialogue: 0,0:01:12.53,0:01:14.59,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Thanks for being so considerate again.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:14.90,0:01:19.78,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,But I've told you a million times \Nthat I can do without breakfast.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:20.33,0:01:22.16,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I can't have that.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:22.16,0:01:23.91,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,You're allowing me to live here.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:23.91,0:01:26.55,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,So it's the least I can do as your attendant.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:27.88,0:01:31.30,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,You're still not a morning person.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:31.30,0:01:33.11,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,That's surprising.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:33.51,0:01:36.74,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Having at least one little quirk like that
Dialogue: 0,0:01:37.51,0:01:39.06,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,gives a girl some charm, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:53.19,0:01:54.51,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Schedule-wise,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:54.51,0:01:57.99,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I have a special lecture on \Ncutting in mineralogy today.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:57.99,0:01:58.88,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,How about you?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:59.37,0:02:02.20,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I think I just have primary subjects all morning.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:02.20,0:02:04.30,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Then we're together half the day.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:04.30,0:02:06.27,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Let's meet at our usual spot this afternoon.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:10.34,0:02:11.15,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Tohsaka...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:12.84,0:02:14.79,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,No, forget it.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:26.64,0:02:27.81,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,What's the matter?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:27.81,0:02:29.29,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Do you know that person?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:29.77,0:02:33.04,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,No, we've just walked by each other a few times.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:34.36,0:02:35.55,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,It wasn't that...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:36.11,0:02:39.36,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,This is a bit belated, but it just \Nhit me how strange this is.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:39.36,0:02:43.79,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Why is an outsider like me being allowed \Nto study magic at a place like this?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:43.79,0:02:45.56,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,For the last time, you aren't an outsider.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:45.83,0:02:48.06,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I told you Clock Tower's rules, remember?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:48.50,0:02:50.96,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,When you're a noted mage's rightful heir,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:50.96,0:02:53.31,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,you're at constant risk of\Nhaving others try to kill you.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:54.00,0:02:56.92,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Given that, a mage has the right
Dialogue: 0,0:02:56.92,0:03:00.95,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,to be accompanied by a follower \Nor pupil for their protection.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:01.43,0:03:04.72,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,You're enrolled here as my follower,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:04.72,0:03:06.58,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,so act a little more dignified.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:07.02,0:03:10.21,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I know that. I'm grateful to you, Tohsaka.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:10.21,0:03:13.82,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,You ought to be. Getting you in wasn't easy.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:14.07,0:03:16.84,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Well, it's only a three-year special exemption.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:17.49,0:03:19.09,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,But be careful.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:19.61,0:03:22.41,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,As a school, this place has rules,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:22.41,0:03:24.72,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,but none of the normal social laws.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:25.08,0:03:27.87,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Even if it's just a "minor" ritual in the Far East,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:27.87,0:03:30.67,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,you're a mage who survived the Holy Grail War.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:30.92,0:03:32.35,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,You did that.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:32.75,0:03:35.25,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Some here won't take kindly to that,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:35.25,0:03:36.36,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,so if you let down your guard...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:36.76,0:03:37.61,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Your guard is down.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:37.88,0:03:39.42,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Guess again!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:45.81,0:03:47.39,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Sherou!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:47.68,0:03:49.14,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Luvia-san?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:49.47,0:03:51.44,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Don't be so impersonal!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:51.44,0:03:54.38,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,You're not currently on the \Nclock as her butler, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:54.77,0:03:58.28,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,"Miss Luvia" is perfectly fine, Sherou!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:59.28,0:04:02.36,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Don't get so chummy with him!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:02.70,0:04:04.95,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, Miss Tohsaka...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:04.95,0:04:06.91,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,We're classmates, as well as neighbors
Dialogue: 0,0:04:06.91,0:04:09.39,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,living in the same apartment building.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:09.79,0:04:12.75,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,What's so inappropriate about that?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:12.75,0:04:14.50,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Everything about it is inappropriate!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:14.50,0:04:16.02,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Relax, Tohsaka.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:16.50,0:04:19.67,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Let's try to get along with our classmates, okay?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:19.96,0:04:24.66,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Anyway, we only got the third floor of that \Nbuilding thanks to Luvia-san, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:24.66,0:04:26.64,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Sherou!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:26.64,0:04:27.62,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Hey!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:31.43,0:04:32.99,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Don't let it go to your head!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:33.31,0:04:36.04,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, dear! O-Oh, oh, oh, oh!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:36.61,0:04:38.23,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Change in plans!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:38.23,0:04:39.67,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Our next class will be...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:44.61,0:04:46.24,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Self-defense.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:46.24,0:04:49.58,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,The class where one expresses one's \Nvitality through physical ability.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:50.04,0:04:52.29,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,The Edelfelt family's designated heir,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:52.29,0:04:54.14,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Luviagelita Edelfelt,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:54.14,0:04:56.56,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,will do you the honor of schooling you.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:20.15,0:05:21.48,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Excellent!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:21.48,0:05:23.74,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,You might be mistaken for a gorilla! Miss Gorilla!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:23.74,0:05:25.38,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,That's right, keep talking!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:27.57,0:05:30.74,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,It hurts! It hurts, it hurts!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:30.99,0:05:33.77,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,What's the deal with that nouveau riche bitch?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:33.77,0:05:38.02,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I nailed her right in the medulla oblongata, \Nso why wouldn't she go down?!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:41.21,0:05:44.01,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Luvia-san isn't a bad person, so just—
Dialogue: 0,0:05:44.01,0:05:46.09,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Where did you two meet, anyway?!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:46.43,0:05:50.82,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Well, not long after we moved here, \Nwe both got lost...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:55.27,0:05:56.58,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Ow, ow, ow! Ow!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:58.86,0:06:00.31,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, well...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:00.31,0:06:02.65,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I'll settle things with her eventually.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:05.45,0:06:07.59,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,So, what will you do?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:08.37,0:06:12.26,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,You got an invitation, right? To officially \Njoin the Mages Association?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:13.45,0:06:14.60,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:15.41,0:06:20.92,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,A mage's natural talents and the color of \Nhis soul are evaluated and recorded.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:20.92,0:06:23.61,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,He then becomes a mage affiliated with Clock Tower.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:24.46,0:06:25.73,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Isn't that a good thing?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:26.05,0:06:28.59,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Your activities would be limited in some ways
Dialogue: 0,0:06:28.59,0:06:30.99,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,because you'd basically be \Nindebted to the Association.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:31.47,0:06:35.18,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,But it comes with a lot of perks for a mage,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:35.18,0:06:37.02,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,so most people would jump at it.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:38.77,0:06:39.75,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:40.56,0:06:41.98,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I guess you're right.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:50.24,0:06:55.25,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Becoming a Clock Tower member \Nand a genuine mage...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:56.50,0:06:57.77,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,It's the right decision.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:58.18,0:07:01.29,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,But what I believed in was...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:16.14,0:07:16.99,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Tohsaka?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:19.81,0:07:23.40,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Sorry, I overslept. I'll start breakfast right now.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:23.40,0:07:24.27,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Emiya-kun...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:26.53,0:07:29.16,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Will you go somewhere with me today?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:53.76,0:07:55.22,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,What is this place?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:55.22,0:07:56.79,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Glastonbury.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:56.79,0:07:59.02,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,A certain king's grave.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:59.31,0:08:00.23,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,That day,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:00.23,0:08:04.29,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,you said you regretted not getting the \Nchance to say a proper goodbye.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:05.61,0:08:08.54,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I'll give you two some time alone.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:18.50,0:08:22.11,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I forgot that you were a king, Saber.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:24.58,0:08:25.79,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:26.13,0:08:29.17,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,For what it's worth, I'm here now, Saber.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:34.93,0:08:36.26,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,This sure is a nice place.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:36.26,0:08:37.77,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, it is.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:37.77,0:08:42.27,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,It feels weird to think that, in a place like this,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:42.27,0:08:45.21,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,people once led lives nothing like ours.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:45.81,0:08:48.27,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Like they say, it's a big old world.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:48.53,0:08:51.28,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,It's already been six months \Nsince we came to England.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:51.28,0:08:53.95,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,For me, every day is one surprise after another.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:53.95,0:08:55.09,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,How about you?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:55.49,0:08:57.39,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,It's the same as you.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:57.39,0:09:00.01,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I've learned how insignificant I am.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:00.01,0:09:03.29,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I became a Master, fought with Saber,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:03.29,0:09:05.60,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,and survived the Holy Grail War, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:05.88,0:09:09.13,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I boasted, "I can do anything \Nif I put my mind to it."
Dialogue: 0,0:09:09.13,0:09:13.30,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,But by the very next day, \Nthat arrogance had faded away.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:13.30,0:09:14.88,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I'm not surprised.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:14.88,0:09:17.87,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,You never change, Shirou.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:18.43,0:09:19.86,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I understand now.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:20.52,0:09:23.88,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,The Holy Grail War was a major event.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:23.88,0:09:26.31,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,But when you see it from the outside like this,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:26.31,0:09:28.38,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,it was only one event of many.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:28.77,0:09:31.09,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,But there are things that were left behind.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:31.09,0:09:33.11,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,And things that will change.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:33.82,0:09:36.45,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I might not have personally matured.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:36.45,0:09:40.92,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,But I just saw for myself \Nhow special that battle was.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:42.75,0:09:44.51,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I'm the opposite.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:44.51,0:09:48.40,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I'm starting to believe it wasn't \Nanything special at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:49.00,0:09:51.21,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,The Holy Grail War, Clock Tower,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:51.21,0:09:53.21,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,simple days like this...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:53.21,0:09:55.55,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,They'll never fundamentally change.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:55.55,0:09:58.18,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,You borrowed Saber's strength,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:58.18,0:10:02.91,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,but in her life, Saber herself relied on\Nthe strength of people of the past.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:03.18,0:10:05.52,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,We're all connected.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:05.52,0:10:08.69,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I think we go through life using \Nnot only our own strength,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:08.69,0:10:11.28,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,but also the hard work of \Nthose who came before.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:11.73,0:10:15.86,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Clock Tower is steeped in ancient traditions.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:15.86,0:10:19.95,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,So every day, while I'm studying, \NI feel like someone is judging me.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:20.58,0:10:24.43,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Like they're saying, "What will you add to this?"
Dialogue: 0,0:10:25.08,0:10:26.54,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, I get it.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:27.29,0:10:29.96,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I guess that's only natural.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:44.35,0:10:47.04,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Hey! Wake up, numbskull!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:54.15,0:10:56.83,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Everyone's already left for the assembly!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:56.83,0:10:59.30,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Are you boycotting it or something?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:00.17,0:11:01.05,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Hurry!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:01.37,0:11:04.56,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,The closing assembly of our\Nsecond year is about to start!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:16.72,0:11:17.94,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Issei...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:17.94,0:11:20.30,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,How are things going on the mountain?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:21.30,0:11:24.45,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,The rebuilding of the main hall just got underway.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:25.27,0:11:27.10,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Everyone is working hard.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:27.39,0:11:31.10,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Times such as these truly \Ntest a head priest's mettle.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:31.44,0:11:34.57,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Admittedly, I'm barely even a novice...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:34.57,0:11:38.24,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,But it's enough to make me want to bow \Nin gratitude to our parishioners.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:38.24,0:11:40.84,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, I'll come by to help out soon.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:41.20,0:11:43.78,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,That reminds me, how is Shinji doing?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:43.78,0:11:46.10,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,He's been in the hospital for quite some time.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:46.54,0:11:48.08,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, don't worry.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:48.08,0:11:50.42,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,He should be discharged any day now.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:50.42,0:11:52.60,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Sakura's been going to visit him daily.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:52.60,0:11:54.98,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, his little sister
Dialogue: 0,0:11:54.98,0:11:57.55,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,is checking in on him every day, eh?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:57.55,0:12:00.97,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, from what I can see, \Nshe's worn Shinji down.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:00.97,0:12:03.05,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Sakura's a tenacious girl,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:03.05,0:12:04.99,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,so he's been browbeaten into \Nletting her look after him.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:06.14,0:12:07.99,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,That's wonderful news.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:15.48,0:12:17.61,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Just the two kids I was looking for!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:22.28,0:12:25.74,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,It's been a month since anyone's heard from him,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:26.08,0:12:30.14,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,and at the start of the new semester, \Na new teacher will be coming.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:30.46,0:12:35.21,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,We'll look after Kuzuki-sensei's \Npersonal effects at the temple.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:35.21,0:12:38.15,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,He turned up at the temple out \Nof nowhere in the first place,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:38.59,0:12:41.42,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,so I suppose it's fitting that \Nhe left us the same way.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:49.89,0:12:51.85,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Well, if it isn't the student council president.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:52.27,0:12:54.42,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Patrolling campus so early in the morning?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:55.06,0:12:58.44,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Or are you making maintenance \Nrounds of the club rooms?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:59.22,0:13:00.32,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Tohsaka!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:00.57,0:13:02.82,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I tire of saying it so often,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:02.82,0:13:05.45,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,but you really are diligent that way, aren't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:06.66,0:13:09.29,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I've grown rather tired of our \Nrote exchanges, myself!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:09.29,0:13:12.00,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Why not chance a different guess\Nevery once in a while?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:12.00,0:13:15.81,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Surely you haven't been deliberately \Nrepeating yourself, Tohsaka!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:16.13,0:13:18.46,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Of course I have.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:18.46,0:13:21.13,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,What? You never figured that out?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:21.13,0:13:23.32,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Ryuudou-kun sure is uptight,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:24.07,0:13:26.24,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,don't you think?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:27.36,0:13:29.74,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Wh-What's the meaning of this, Emiya?!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:30.06,0:13:33.44,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,What manner of relationship are \Nyou in with this foul vixen?!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:33.44,0:13:34.20,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Uh, I...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:34.60,0:13:37.61,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Anyway, come get me in my \Nclassroom later, Emiya-kun.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:37.61,0:13:39.71,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I'll wait until you get there.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:40.11,0:13:41.74,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Wh-What in the world?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:41.74,0:13:45.84,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Oh! There you are, president!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:46.57,0:13:48.95,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Mitsuzuri Ayako...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:48.95,0:13:52.91,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,President, would you mind explaining that budget?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:52.91,0:13:55.87,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Why is my club's budget the one to get slashed?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:55.87,0:13:57.60,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,The archery club isn't the only one!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:57.92,0:14:01.30,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,All club budgets have had to be reviewed.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:01.30,0:14:03.11,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I don't buy it!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:03.54,0:14:06.50,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,You'll stand right there and explain yourself!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:12.56,0:14:13.89,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Say, Emiya-kun...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:14.18,0:14:16.35,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Were you ever in the track club?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:16.35,0:14:18.00,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Track club?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:18.00,0:14:21.44,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,No, I was always in the archery club.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:21.86,0:14:22.92,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Oh...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:23.32,0:14:26.11,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Well, I guess these things happen.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:26.61,0:14:28.88,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,When I was looking at the sunset, \Nsome memories came back.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:29.41,0:14:32.62,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,You have to admit, it's flown by in a flash...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:32.62,0:14:38.55,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,It's been a month since the Holy Grail War \Nended and you signed on as my pupil.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:38.55,0:14:41.54,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,At this rate, the next year will fly by.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:41.84,0:14:45.28,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,After that happens, we'll be \Nleaving this school behind.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:46.34,0:14:49.13,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,What do you plan to do after graduation?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:50.05,0:14:52.03,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Follow in your father's footsteps?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:52.33,0:14:54.98,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Uh, yeah... Why?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:54.98,0:14:58.52,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,After I graduate, I'm going to London.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:58.77,0:15:02.54,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,After all that's happened, the Mages Association \Ngave me a letter of recommendation.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:02.86,0:15:06.61,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,London? The Mages Association's headquarters?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:06.61,0:15:08.05,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,That Clock Tower place?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:08.61,0:15:12.45,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I've been invited as the Tohsaka family heir.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:12.45,0:15:16.37,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,They say I can bring a pupil with me if I like.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:17.12,0:15:19.24,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Um, does that mean...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:21.08,0:15:21.95,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,So.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:23.17,0:15:25.06,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,What will you be doing?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:26.97,0:15:31.74,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Damn it, you always go right for my weak spot.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:31.74,0:15:32.94,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:33.72,0:15:34.76,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Look...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:35.14,0:15:38.37,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,This is important, so give me a straight answer.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:38.85,0:15:41.50,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Will you come with me?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:44.90,0:15:47.76,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Don't ask when you already know the answer.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:49.11,0:15:52.01,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Then let's continue to have a productive \Nrelationship, Emiya-kun!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:53.12,0:15:58.50,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I'm gonna whip you into shape until you're \Na proper mage, so brace yourself!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:58.75,0:16:03.38,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,My life's goal is to make you into a new man,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:03.38,0:16:05.18,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,one who's thoroughly happy.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:16.35,0:16:19.29,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Thanks for bringing me with you.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:56.12,0:16:56.99,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Excuse me.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:57.68,0:17:00.82,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,You are the exchange student from Japan?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:01.85,0:17:03.87,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Actually, that would be Tohsaka.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:04.19,0:17:05.76,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I know that.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:06.40,0:17:09.32,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I was referring to you.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:09.32,0:17:11.51,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,You're from Fuyuki City, in Japan, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:12.28,0:17:14.95,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,You don't seem to have the makings of a mage.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:14.95,0:17:17.91,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I imagine you were an outsider who was
Dialogue: 0,0:17:17.91,0:17:21.29,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,caught up in the ritual and missed \Nhis chance to get out?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:21.79,0:17:23.71,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I find it puzzling.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:23.71,0:17:26.92,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,After surviving that troublesome war,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:26.92,0:17:29.51,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,to what end have you come to Clock Tower?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:29.96,0:17:32.30,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,To what end do you study magic?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:33.88,0:17:35.16,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Good question.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:36.09,0:17:38.51,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Since coming here, I've learned many things,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:38.51,0:17:41.04,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,and in many ways, I've been out of my depth.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:41.85,0:17:45.07,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,But I want to keep believing in \Nwhat I believed in before.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:45.07,0:17:48.27,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I want to dedicate my life to that.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:48.73,0:17:50.29,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Meaning what, exactly?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:50.61,0:17:54.32,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Well, I realize how dumb this sounds...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:55.41,0:17:57.23,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,But I want to become something.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:59.24,0:18:01.26,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,A hero of justice.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:05.54,0:18:08.71,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I see. That certainly is idiotic.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:08.71,0:18:10.22,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,But it is not humorous.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:11.25,0:18:12.89,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,A hero of justice, you say?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:14.05,0:18:17.33,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,This place is, indeed, a small world.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:26.39,0:18:27.60,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Tohsaka?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:27.60,0:18:29.96,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Did we have plans for dinner?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:31.82,0:18:33.46,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I was waiting for you.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:35.15,0:18:37.72,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Well? What did you do about enrollment?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:39.03,0:18:40.97,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, I turned them down.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:43.24,0:18:45.37,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,You aren't angry?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:46.04,0:18:48.69,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I knew this would happen.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:48.69,0:18:52.66,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, but if you aren't going to join Clock Tower,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:52.66,0:18:55.99,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I guess that means I'll be thrown \Nout in three years, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:56.38,0:18:58.76,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,No, that doesn't mean you have to—
Dialogue: 0,0:19:02.06,0:19:03.85,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Are you sure, though?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:03.85,0:19:06.39,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I've been thinking about it nonstop,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:06.39,0:19:09.85,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,but I don't think I'll ever be \Nable to change how I live.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:09.85,0:19:14.50,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Even when I know I'm not right, \NI can't change paths.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:18.03,0:19:19.70,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,It's just as he said...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:19.70,0:19:21.83,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I'll meet the same fate.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:21.83,0:19:24.58,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,He's right. I agree with him there.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:24.58,0:19:26.64,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,You're full of mistakes, Shirou.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:27.08,0:19:31.17,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,You're probably on the same path, \Nheading in the same direction.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:31.42,0:19:35.42,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,The difference might be in how far you can go.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:35.84,0:19:41.26,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,What matters is where you end up, \Nand how far you came, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:41.26,0:19:44.41,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Even if your destination and the \Nresult end up being the same,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:44.41,0:19:47.60,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,if you manage to walk a little further afterward,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:47.60,0:19:50.85,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I know you'll get your proper ending.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:51.46,0:19:52.48,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:52.94,0:19:55.13,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I really hope it turns out like that.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:55.57,0:19:59.45,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,No, I guess I'll have to ensure \Nthat that's what happens.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:59.45,0:20:00.88,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I wouldn't worry.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:01.32,0:20:04.64,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I mean, you've had your answer all along.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:05.16,0:20:06.51,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,But are you really sure?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:07.04,0:20:10.96,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Clock Tower is an important place to you, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:10.96,0:20:12.63,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I'll be fine.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:12.63,0:20:15.15,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,In the end, I'll probably settle \Ndown at Clock Tower.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:15.15,0:20:18.55,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,But I want to look around and \Nget stuff out of my system.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:18.55,0:20:20.53,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,You know, see the world.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:20.84,0:20:24.16,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,So now it's my turn to drag \Nyou around with me, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:24.55,0:20:27.68,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, though that's all a ways off yet.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:29.31,0:20:34.42,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Regardless, having fun, suffering, \Nseeing the sights,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:34.81,0:20:37.80,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,and eventually having our \Nown happily ever after.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:40.65,0:20:43.43,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,That's the future in store for us.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:40.40,0:22:42.44,Default - italics,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,A boy once said,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:42.90,0:22:45.19,Default - italics,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,"I don't want to watch people die."
Dialogue: 0,0:22:45.82,0:22:47.61,Default - italics,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,If people can be saved,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:47.61,0:22:51.18,Default - italics,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,could it be possible to save every \Nperson that's suffering?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:52.37,0:22:56.41,Default - italics,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,What the boy was trying to cut down was himself.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:57.00,0:22:59.95,Default - italics,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,He wielded his sword for what \Nhe came to believe in.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:01.38,0:23:05.69,Default - italics,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,There is no longer a path where his \Nbattle ends and he turns back.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:07.26,0:23:09.94,Default - italics,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,However, he did get his answer.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:09.94,0:23:11.68,Default - italics,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,He has regrets.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:11.68,0:23:15.16,Default - italics,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,And he doesn't know how many times \Nhe has wished to do it all over.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:15.64,0:23:18.02,Default - italics,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,This fate is set in stone,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:18.02,0:23:20.39,Default - italics,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,and Emiya will probably go on cursing it.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:21.33,0:23:22.94,Default - italics,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,But even still,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:23.44,0:23:27.28,Default - italics,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I was not wrong.
